feat(library): Phase 19a — MCP server registry UI + 10 new bun RPCs

New "Library" panel as a left-edge activity-bar sidebar (pi-book
icon), hosting global/cross-session config. First tab: MCP servers.

Library panel:
- LibraryPanel.vue is a PrimeVue Tabs container (MCP + Skills).
  Active tab persists in localStorage.
- Registered as `library` component in main.ts.
- Activity-bar item at initial-size 360 / minimum 280.

MCP tab (LibraryMcpTab.vue + McpServerForm.vue):
- Configured list with per-row enable/disable toggle (writes the
  SDK global allowlist), Edit / Remove / Sign-in buttons.
- Discovered list with Enable shortcut for servers not yet configured.
- Add dialog: structured form (transport switch, command/args/env
  or url/headers/oauth fields) with View-as-JSON toggle that
  round-trips through JSON.parse + structured re-population.
- Inline OAuth "Sign in" calls session-scoped mcp.oauth.login and
  opens the returned authorizationUrl via the renderer's openUrl.

Skills tab stub (LibrarySkillsTab.vue): rendered already but the
right-rail "manage globally" link lands in 19b. The 19b-side RPCs
(discoverSkills, setGloballyDisabledSkills) shipped here so 19b
reduces to wiring polish.

10 new bun RPCs threaded through src-bun/rpc.ts → src/ipc/types.ts
→ src-bun/index.ts handlers → src-bun/test-server.ts mirrors:
- listMcpConfigs / addMcpConfig / updateMcpConfig / removeMcpConfig
- enableMcpServers / disableMcpServers / discoverMcpServers
- loginToMcpServer (session-scoped)
- discoverSkills / setGloballyDisabledSkills

fakeClient gets in-memory mcpConfigs + mcpDisabled + skillsDisabled
sets plus stub responses for discover so E2E flows can mutate
without a real CLI.

E2E F18 (18-library-mcp.pwtest.ts) covers open / add / JSON
round-trip. 64/64 E2E green (prod + HMR), 386 bun unit tests.

Boot-verified with `bun run dev` + log tail + Playwright screenshot
of both MCP and Skills tabs at default rail size (per personal anti-
regression rule 3a).

Decisions captured in DEVLOG: edge panel over dockview body,
session-reuse for OAuth, opt-in JSON mode, per-server tool listing
deferred until SDK exposes it.

